.TH YAML_HAS_PENDING_EVENTS 3 "2026-06-30" "libyaml 0.1.0" "libyaml library"
.SH NAME
yaml_has_pending_events, yaml_event_count \- event queue inspection
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <yaml.h>
.PP
.BI "int yaml_has_pending_events(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.BI "size_t yaml_event_count(yaml_ctx_t *" ctx ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR yaml_has_pending_events ()
checks whether the context's event queue contains at least one event
waiting to be dequeued via
.BR yaml_next_event ().
Returns 1 if events are available, 0 otherwise.
.PP
.BR yaml_event_count ()
returns the total number of events currently in the queue.
This is useful for pre-allocating buffers or determining how many
.BR yaml_next_event ()
calls can be made without blocking.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.BR yaml_has_pending_events ()
returns 1 if events are pending, 0 if the queue is empty.
.PP
.BR yaml_event_count ()
returns the number of events in the queue as a
.IR size_t .
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
yaml_feed_input(ctx, data, len);
while (yaml_has_pending_events(ctx)) {
    yaml_event_t ev;
    yaml_next_event(ctx, &ev);
    /* process ev */
}
.fi
.SH THREAD SAFETY
Not thread-safe. Use from a single thread at a time.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR yaml_next_event (3),
.BR yaml_feed_input (3),
.BR yaml_event_count (3)
